name: EVEN TRUE Pore Refining Gel Cleanser
description: This lightweight foaming cleanser gently removes impurities and excess oil without stripping or over-drying. An exclusive combination of pore-clarifying ingredients purify skin and minimizes pores for a smoother appearance cleanse skin and minimize pores for a smoother appearance. Antioxidants Green Tea and Vitamin E help protect against damaging environmental elements while skin-brightening ingredients like Turmeric promote a glowing, healthy complexion.Approved for all skin types.

name: XeraCalm A.D Lipid-Replenishing Cleansing Oil
description: Avène's ultra-gentle cleanser is formulated with eczema in mind, though it's great for regularly dry or itchy skin, too.

name: Hydrating Facial Cleanser for Normal to Dry Skin
description: Three cheers for CeraVe. The drugstore staple uses ceramides and hyaluronic acid in its hydrating cleanser—a moisture-attracting ingredient that complements the whole face wash process

name: Cetaphil's Gentle Skin Cleanser
description: The Cetaphil Gentle Skin Cleanser lives up to its name in that it's notably gentle with only eight ingredients, its main one being water. It's great for use on all skin types, has a mild and non-irritating formula, and will soften your skin for a healthy glow. Cetaphil also won't clog your pores, thanks to its non-comedogenic and non-alkaline formula. It's also fragrance- and soap-free, too, so it's almost like using pure water and lotion mixed together.

name: Tula Replenishing Cleansing Oil
description: Key ingredients: Ceramides, probiotic extracts, rice bran oil, arctic winged kelp. Tula Replenishing Cleansing Oil removes makeup easily and cleanses more. Infused with probiotic extracts and natural oils, the product will effectively dissolve makeup and built-on debris from the day. The mixture of ceramides and arctic winged kelp (yes, algae) aids in moisture retention and skin-soothing, too.

name: Fresh Soy Makeup Removing Face Wash
description: Key ingredients: Soy, cucumber, rosewater, borage seed oil.The Fresh Soy Makeup Removing Face Wash is recommended for all skin types and is rich in soy amino acids to help maintain skin elasticity. Calming cucumber extract and borage seed oil help soothe the skin, while the rosewater helps to balance and calm the skin.  The Fresh wash doesn't strip your skin either and is formulated vegan and void of gluten and parabens. And, with it targeting dull, dry, and uneven textures, you'll notice vivacious skin before you know it.

name: Naturium's Niacinamide Cleansing Gel
description: Key ingredients: Glycerin, niacinamide, hyaluronic acidSensitive skin is one thing, but sensitive and dry skin is another. Naturium Niacinamide Cleansing Gel 3% — a vegan pore-minimizer that contains both glycerin and niacinamide to effectively replenish your skin's surface.For dry skin, a face wash with glycerin, ceramides, or niacinamide can help to repair or protect the skin against environmental stressors. Niacinamide helps to restore your skin's barrier, while glycerin is rich in nutrients and a humectant that draws water back into the skin for ultimate hydration. Natrium is cruelty, gluten, and paraben-free. Dermatologist-tested

name: Farmacy Whipped Greens Foaming Cleanser
description: Key ingredients: Beta hydroxy, glycerin, moringa seed extract, moringa water, papaya enzyme, green clay, sodium PCA. The Farmacy Whipped Greens Foaming Cleanser is wonderful for oily skin and not just because it's oil-free — it's also soap-free, super creamy, and uniquely contains moringa seed extract and moringa water to purify and refresh the skin from debris.It also contains papaya enzyme and green clay ingredients that help detox, absorb surface oil, exfoliate, clean pores, and remove buildup. Sodium PCA also aids in maintaining skin hydration. It's also cruelty-free, gluten-free, and comes in recyclable packaging.

name: Superfood Antioxidant Cleanser
description: Key ingredients: Glycerin, kale, spinach, green tea.Superfood Antioxidant Cleanser is a powerful blend of all the healthful green ingredients with overarching health benefits: kale to give your skin an extra glow, spinach to soothe the skin, and green tea to fight visible signs of aging. It is also vegan; cruelty-, gluten-, and paraben-free, and comes in recyclable packaging for an easy and sustainable toss.

name: Paula's choice moisturizing lotion
description: Fortified with a proprietary blend of brightening peptides and natural citrus extracts to improve skin's radiance and reverse hyper-pigmentation. Enriched with nourishing African-origin oils and butters that help skin retain moisture and protect against environmental damage.

name: La Roche-Posay Toleriane Double Repair Face Moisturizer
description: Contains ceramides, niacinamide, glycerin. If your skin is sensitive, this moisturizer from La Roche Posay is a good option. It  contains a host of the ingredients recommended by the dermatologists, including ceramides, glycerin, and niacinamide. Garshick likes this moisturizer for sensitive skin types in particular, noting the soothing, skin-barrier supporting ingredients. It also has an SPF of 30, which offers an added layer of protection and helps to protect skin from aging further.

name: CeraVe Moisturising Cream
description: Contains ceramides, hyaluronic acid, glycerin | Does not contain retinol | Rich cream. This moisturizer helps replenish hyaluronic acid  which is what makes it such an effective skin hydrator and plumper. In addition to being packed with key ingredients, this moisturizer is also fragrance-free, making it suitable for those with sensitive skin, and it doesn't feel greasy.

name: OLAY Regenerist Micro-Sculpting Cream
description: Contains niacinamide, hyaluronic acid, glycerin, peptides | Does not contain retinol | Rich cream.The powerhouse ingredient helps to stop the transfer of melanin pigments to skin cells and also acts as a humectant, preventing additional moisture loss in the skin. It also contains glycerin, hyaluronic acid, and aloe — which work together to hydrate and soothe skin.

name: Vichy Aqualia Thermal Rich Cream Moisturizer

description: For an oil-free moisturizer, this one is surprisingly moisturizing without being too much for those with oily, acne-prone skin, but it's ideal for someone with skin that falls right in the middle and needs a boost of hydration. It also contains vitamin C, ginger, turmeric, niacinamide, and antioxidants to help brighten dark spots

name: NIVEA Soft Moisturizing Cream

name: Hyper Skin Fade and Glow AHA Mask
description: Hyper Skin's Fade and Glow AHA Mask contains a winning combo of two of the most effective AHAs (or alpha hydroxy acids) — five percent glycolic acid and five percent mandelic acid — to gently exfoliate the skin and get rid of congestion. This mask also contains niacinamide and bearberry to fade dark spots and soften the skin. This makes this mask ideal for people who currently have acne-prone skin since it's so decongesting, but it also helps those looking to treat older scars and smoothen their skin.

name: Then I Met You Rosé Resurfacing Facial Mask
description: For the perfect mix of high-tech ingredients and tried-and-true favorites, you can't go wrong with Korean skin-care brand Then I Met You. "With a blend of 6% glycolic and lactic acids, this is a great option for people looking for a light exfoliation along with an antioxidant boost. Containing a new ingredient in the skin-care space — resveratrol, derived from red grapes — the Resurfacing Facial Mask also helps to smoothen the skin over time.

name: The Inkey List Kaolin Mask
description: Kaolin Mask by The Inkey List contains a potent combination of both kaolin and smectite clay, this mask sucks up excess oil, especially in acneic skin. Still, it's probably best not to use this type of face mask every day, since that may dry up the skin too much and cause your cells to actually create more oil to help balance the skin out.  ideal for very dry sensitive skin.

name: Summer Fridays Jet Lag Mask
description: This is a calming mask for skin that's on the more sensitive side and might deal with conditions like eczema or redness. "Summer Fridays Jet Lag Mask is an anti-inflammatory, hydrating mask that can also be used as a leave-on moisturizer. Glycerin, ceramides, and hyaluronic acid give dry skin a hydration boost, while niacinamide and cucumber help calm the skin of inflammation. ideal for very dry sensitive skin.

name: Kora Organics Turmeric BHA Hydrating Treatment Mask
description: Kora Organics Turmeric BHA Hydrating Treatment Mask contains plant-based ingredients like rosehip, peppermint, and turmeric that serves as a physical exfoliant containing mineral powder. "After five to 15 minutes, the instructions to remove the mask include using circular motions to allow for a physical exfoliation." This helps to not only clear clogged pores, but also to diminish the appearance of scars and blemishes by removing dead skin cells and debris.

name: Kora Organics Turmeric BHA Hydrating Treatment Mask
description: When it comes to acne-fighting masks, the GlamGlow Supermud Clearing Treatment is a game-changer. After leaving it on for 10 minutes, you can visibly see the oil drawn out from your pores, and after rinsing, skin is left looking brighter than ever. ideal for oily and sensitive skin

name: Paula's Choice Super Hydrate Overnight Mask
description: Paula's Choice Super Hydrate Overnight Mask is a great choice for anyone, but especially those with dry and sensitive skin. The cream-gel formula is infused with calming reishi mushroom, soothing algae, shea butter, and glycerin to lock in moisture while you snooze away. Come morning, you'll wake up to plumper, dewier skin. However, you can also use it as a 20-minute wash-off mask depending on your preferences
